snippet: The Archdiocese of Milwaukee said that it was prepared to set aside $4 million in its bankruptcy reorganization plan to compensate victims of clergy sexual abuse.
abstract: Archdiocese of Milwaukee says it is prepared to set aside $4 million in its bankruptcy reorganization plan to compensate victims of clergy sexual abuse; amount is criticized by one victim for being too small.
lead_paragraph: The Archdiocese of Milwaukee said that it was prepared to set aside $4 million in its bankruptcy reorganization plan to compensate victims of clergy sexual abuse.

headline.main: Wisconsin: Archdiocese Offers $4 Million to Abuse Victims
